==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Licensed
<hw>Li"censed</hw> <pr>(l⟦imac⟧"s⟦eit⟧nst)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<def>Having a license; permitted or authorized by license; <as>as, a
<ex>licensed</ex> victualer; a <ex>licensed</ex> traffic.</as></def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> accredited, commissioned, licenced.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Licensed victualer</b></col>, <cd>one who has a license
to keep an inn or eating house; esp., a victualer who has a license to
sell intoxicating liquors.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Licensee</ent>⟦br⟧
